I have a minor comment though. I think it will be great if we can add unit tests,example topology and doc for this.

I've also been thinking about this as a way to simplfy the packing algorithms. I'd like to reduce the number of Maps and Collections passed around in that code and replace with a builder, specifically the `Map<Integer, List<InstanceId>> resource` that is used, as well as some of our shared `PackingUtil` static helpers. I've looked at the code a bit and I think an impl like this would work to encapsulate building/modifying packing plans:

```
public class PackingPlanBuilder {
  PackingPlanBuidler()
  PackingPlanBuidler(PackingPlan existingPacking)

  // topology settings
  void setTopologyId(String topologyId);

  // set resource settings
  void setDefaultInstanceResource(Resource resource);
  void setRequestedComponentRam(String componentName, long ram);
  void setRequestedContainerRam(long ram);
  void setRequestedContainerRamPadding(long ram);

  // add or remove instances
  void addInstance(Integer containerId, InstanceId instance);
  void removeInstance(Integer containerId, InstanceId instance);
  void removeAnyInstance(String componentName);

  // build container plan sets by summing up instance resources
  // mostly impl from PackingUtils.buildContainerPlans
  PackingPlan build() throws InvalidPackingExcepton;
}
```

cc/ @avflor @ashvina who have also been thinking about this.
